The paper deals with a fundamental way of comparing evolutionary trees, which is a topic that falls under computational biology. However, the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspect of computing the subtree prune-and-regraft (SPR) distance metric, which involves graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
